                  <ab type="history">Dabr. A few nuns residing in a separated building in the compound. An additional small church dedicated to <persName ref="PRS6951Mazgaba" type="tabot">Mazgabā Śǝllāse</persName> 
                     (a head of the monastery Gunda Gunde, <date>17th-early 18th century</date>) stands nearby in the gorge of river <placeName ref="LOC4700MayQar">Qarni</placeName>. It is said to have been built at the place where <persName ref="PRS6951Mazgaba">Mazgabā Śǝllāse</persName> used to pray.</ab>
